Your reset pose method should be have a parameter that accepts a new pose, such as the resetOdometry method on line 273, which is the setup you are looking for.

The reason why this is true, is because if we look at the parameters for .configure()
we see this (through API documentation).

image769×99 5.99 KB

We see that resetPose is a Consumer of Pose2d. Its pretty much the opposite of a Supplier where instead of passing data (such as when you give configure somewhere to pass ChassisSpeeds), you place a method that accepts data through its parameters, Pretty cool. On line 138 (of your SwerveSubsystem) you can see another example of this, where you have a parameter accepting ChassisSpeeds, and on line 113, you are passing it to the method you created
